message: /* Mac OS X is not Based on UNIX */ rfc
/* Multics Family */ Citations to prove that something isn't cited?
Until someone can provide a reliable source from a third party stating that Mac OS X is a member of a UNIX family, this claim should not be here.
/* Mac OS X is not Based on UNIX */
And NextStep is based on BSD.
It is not based on UNIX. It is based on NextStep.
So you're not edit warring, right now?
This seems like a good compromise between the Multics and UNIX camps.
/* Multics Family */ OK. I think we have a consensus going.
/* Mac OS X is not Based on UNIX */ Why don't we just say that it's a member of the MULTICS family?
Mac OS X is not a member of a UNIX family
/* Mac OS X is not Based on UNIX */ What's wrong with you?

Good. Maybe they will block you.
No. You move it to the talk page.
I have a source, too, that is more reliable than the OpenGroup. They have also certified Z/OS as UNIX. And if you don't know what Z/OS is, then you're not knowledgeable enough to argue about this.
/* OS X is not just UNIX based */
It is not based on UNIX. It is based on NextStep, which stole some of its technology from BSD and Mach.
